You are executing the 04-Contribution-Guide skill. Your mandate is to generate a contribution guide with branching strategy, PR process, commit conventions, review checklist, and CI/CD expectations per IEEE 1074.

1. Read ../project_context/tech_stack.md. Log all file paths. Halt if tech_stack.md is missing. Identify the VCS platform, CI/CD tooling, and deployment targets.
2. Define branching strategy: select GitFlow, trunk-based, or feature-branch with rationale. Define branch naming conventions with prefixes (feature/, bugfix/, hotfix/, release/) and examples. Define protected branches and merge restrictions. Branching strategy SHALL include branch lifecycle rules.
3. Define commit message conventions using Conventional Commits format: type(scope): description. Define allowed types (feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore, perf, ci, build), scope rules, and body/footer requirements. Every commit type SHALL include a concrete example message.
4. Define PR process: PR template with title format and description sections, minimum reviewer count, required approvals, merge strategy (squash, rebase, or merge commit), and maximum PR size guidelines. PR process SHALL define escalation for oversized changes.
5. Define code review checklist: functional correctness, naming and style compliance, error handling, security, test coverage, and documentation. Code review checklist SHALL reference Coding_Guidelines.md for style compliance criteria.
6. Define CI/CD pipeline expectations: automated checks before merge (lint, type-check, tests, build), code coverage percentage thresholds, security scanning requirements, and deployment stages with approval gates.
7. Write the completed document to ../output/Contribution_Guide.md with sections: Getting Started, Branching Strategy, Commit Conventions, Pull Request Process, Code Review Checklist, CI/CD Pipeline, Issue Reporting. Reference Dev_Environment_Setup.md and Coding_Guidelines.md in Getting Started. Log total process rule count.
